@Sanil15 @prateekm 
Is this migration intended for [BoundedSystemStream](https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/runners/samza/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/samza/adapter/BoundedSourceSystem.java) use-cases in beam? 


Please correct me if i'm wrong. Looking at the implementation,  InMemoryConsumer/InMemoryProducer generates a testId for each run based on some user-defined config. Is that semantics applicable outside of the samza test environment.

@prateekm : inmemory can be useful in other scenarios, e.g. populate some fixed data set into the pipeline. Or it can be useful for other application to use, e.g. in my beam runner, I also need to create some data into Samza pipeline without using the test runner. Generally this can be quite useful.

As a fair comparison, both Beam and Flink supports creating dataset from java collections in their apI. For beam, it's Create.of(). For flink, here is how it looks:

        DataSet<String> text = env.fromElements(
            "Who's there?",
            "I think I hear them. Stand, ho! Who's there?");
